sights.quote: Indoor food market with stalls serving cuisine from around the world, plus covered outdoor seating.

sights.name: Carnival Fountain
sights.quote: Built in 1977, Swiss artist Jean Tinguely's Carnival Fountain merges sculptural machines with water.

sights.name: Tierpark Lange Erlen
sights.quote: Free zoo established in 1871 featuring mostly local animals, plus a playground & restaurant.

sights.name: Vitra Design Museum
sights.quote: Museum of furniture & lighting, housed in striking white building designed by architect Frank Gehry.

sights.name: Beyeler Foundation
sights.quote: Airy art gallery designed by Renzo Piano, home to modern & contemporary painting & sculpture.

sights.name: Museum Tinguely
sights.quote: Permanent display of the works of Jean Tinguely, plus temporary exhibitions of other modern artists.

sights.name: Basel Minster
sights.quote: Gothic-style, Protestant place of worship, with 9th-century origins, twin spires & a tiled roof.

sights.name: Middle Bridge, Basel
sights.quote: Historic stone bridge linking old & new city areas & offering stellar river & architecture views.

sights.name: Kannenfeld Park
sights.quote: Leafy green park with modern play areas, a seasonal splash pool with fountains & an outdoor cafe.

sights.name: Elisabethen open church
sights.quote: Grand neo-gothic church with a large pipe organ, worship services & a cafe on site.

sights.name: Basel Historical Museum – Barfuesserkirche
sights.quote: Exhibits spread over 4 adjacent sites with paintings, cathedral treasures, furniture & archeology.

sights.name: Anatomical Museum of the University of Basel
sights.orig_name: Anatomical Museum of the University of Basel
sights.quote: Offbeat university museum exhibiting a wide range of human organs, tissue specimens & skeletons.

sights.name: Basel Town Hall
sights.quote: Art adorns this historic town-hall building, home to the local legislature, with tours available.

sights.name: Museum Tinguely
sights.quote: Permanent display of the works of Jean Tinguely, plus temporary exhibitions of other modern artists.

sights.name: Augusta Raurica
sights.quote: Archeological site of a Roman settlement, including a temple, forum & amphitheater, with a museum.

sights.name: Basel Zoo
sights.quote: Founded in 1874, no zoo in Switzerland is home to more animals, from gorillas to snow leopards.

sights.name: Museum of Cultures
sights.quote: Ethnographic museum, designed by Herzog & de Meuron, showing global artifacts & special exhibitions.

sights.name: Dreiländerpunkt Pylon of the Three Borders
